gdob - Git Delete Old Branches

USAGE:
    gdob [--delete-period=period] [--delete-dryrun]

DESCRIPTION:
    Delete old branches based on configuration settings.

OPTIONS:
    --delete-period=period
        Delete branches older than this period
        (conf_git_delete_period)

    --delete-dryrun
        Perform a dry run without actually deleting
        (conf_git_delete_dryrun)

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-git-delete-period=PERIOD
        Default period for branch deletion

    -conf-git-delete-dryrun=0|1
        Enable dry run mode by default

EXAMPLES:
    gdob
    gdob --delete-period="3 months"
    gdob --delete-dryrun